# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# aar-deploy — repository content policy
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is a deployable GitHub Pages repo. The ONLY files that may be
# committed are:
#   - README.md
#   - the deployable web app (index.html and any companion .js/.css/asset
#     files in directories like js/, css/, assets/)
#   - this .gitignore
#
# Everything else — CCCT scaffolding (.claude/, docs/, AGENTS.md,
# CLAUDE.md, .phase_state.json, cognitive_cookie_cutter_template/,
# package.json, tsconfig.json, etc.) and OS/IDE cruft — must NEVER be
# committed. See docs/ccct_deviations.md D-003 for the full policy.
#
# Implementation: ignore everything by default, then explicitly unignore
# the few paths that are part of the deliverable.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Ignore everything at the repo root by default.
/*

# Allow the policy file itself.
!.gitignore

# Allow the project README.
!README.md

# Allow the deployable site files (created in Phase 5).
!index.html
!js/
!css/
!assets/
!favicon.ico
!favicon.png
